	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				     Hail all! I thought i'd share some of my Magician info with you, and some good places to level up quick! so here we go =). During my time as a mage, i've noticed that no other class can solo baddies like we mages can with the exception of the necro and druid. there were even times when i took some Reds! here are some good places to level. You can probaly Solo these places if you choose like i did. ( level alot faster ).  1-5: your newbie zone is the best place. 5-10: East commonlands was great for me ( watch the occasional Giffion ) 10-16: North Ro was great with the Derv camps. 16-22: Highpass orc side worked extremely well, it took me 4 days to go through them, 22-35: highkeep was great, just make sure theres a group around controling the spawns and pick yourself a corner or join a group. 35-40 Lower Guk was fun, Need a group or your toast =) 40+ Soluesk B. called one of the most deadliest dungeons in the game, they mean it. With the right group you should do fine. Trains happen alot and be prepared to run! hehe. I also found researching pretty much useless for me as you can buy all your important spells at your local guild. But you should research because at some levels you cant buy a certain type of pet like Earth, fire etc... Also the upgrades to summon food and water cannot be bought so researching them helps save time ( and mana ). Lets see... Your basic Eqp. should be anything that gives more INT because thats what matters for a mage. I wouldnt worry about using weapons so much later in the game. Its best to have held +INT items in you inventory instead of a weapon ( Your spells subside this with your pet ). Ok, pets. I find earth to be the best Overall. seems to have the most Hps and attacks Fairly well. Be sure to keep an eye on your pet though, as monsters will attack it as they would you. To kill off a pet, either zone or invis yourself. Now for some strats. Early levels you can save your pet sometimes by runnign up and taking some damage while it pounds away. Some Mage DD (Direct Damage) spells are bolts which are best used only in outside or open areas. Bolt spells also may not have anything within its path or the bolt will miss. Mages in PvP status: Do not use AE rain spells / Bolt spells that are in direct line of your pet. If you hit the pet, it will come and start bashing you giving the opponent a Advantage. i found we can take almost any class No pronlem except Necros who also have a pet advantage. About mage damage spells: Mages have the second most damage DD spells in the game. at times, we do more damage then wizards! of course Wizards blow us away DD wise past level 39 though, but not so much =). We et no Teleports or DOT spells, but we can basicaly live on our own being able to summon just about anything, anywhere From Bandages, To Weapons, to Food and more. All in All, i find the mage to be one of the most Funniest class to play. If your looking to have the DD skills of a wizard, and being able to live on your own, a Mage is the prefect class for you.<BR>
<BR>
-Xaladar Darkwind, Tunare
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
