	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				About that guy who wanted to know which class he should choose,<BR>
<BR>
I personally thing that if you only play for an hour at a time, that the Wizard class would be better for you. Here are my reasons.<BR>
<BR>
1) Pets require Regeants. That's part of the reason why most of us just pick a place to lvl, summon until you get a good pet, then stay there for the day. If you're only going to be playing for an hour it sort of makes the whole equation inefficient. On top of that you'd have to make trips back to town to buy more regeant, unless you're rich and can buy 40+ at a time.<BR>
<BR>
2) Conjured items dissappear when you log. So you'd show up in the game, waste about 10 minutes summoning all the stuff you need for your stay in EQ and medding back to full mana. Then you'd leave in like 45 minutes, yeah minus 5 to get to where you want to be.<BR>
<BR>
3) Your comment about traveling is mighty true, but I suppose the Magician counter to it is that you should have made friends by the time you would get traveling spells as a Wizard or Druid that can help you out.<BR>
<BR>
4) The only minus for all those reasons why you should be a Wizard some lvls Wizards need to group, and finding a group can take a while.<BR>
<BR>
Although I'm not telling you what to do, you should decide what you enjoy playing more than what you think you should be playing. I personally love having a pet when I watch my lvl 20 Wizard's Root not work.. Heh at least if you know when you're getting beat you have a chance to flee... disposable tanks (drools).. Wizards learn that they're going to lose when there hardest hitting spell does 5 damage instead of the 200 it's supposed to do, or when the root doesn't work. But that's just my opinion.<BR>
<BR>
Lune, lvl 16 Magician on Povar
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
